{"parentUuid":"ee74afb5-cf0b-4ead-9e5a-b4ff4ea53993","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"4c2d7a20-38ca-44b0-9bfb-bba57b1b8f09","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"A prior multi-agent investigation produced these findings. Use them as\ngrounded context to plan the next step. Do not re-investigate the same\nquestion — assume the findings are correct unless you find direct\nevidence to the contrary.\n\nTopic: new-skill-prompt\nRun ID: 1f20f76f73c6\n\n## Investigation findings\n\n# Investigation: new-skill-prompt\n\n**Status:** confirmed\n**Started:** 2026-05-19\n\n## TLDR\n\nEntire misses sessions in this workflow because the failure is two-sided,\nnot just a skill gap. Producer side: `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv` is its\nown non-Entire-enabled repo, so a parent-launched run has no repo session\nstate for Entire to attach from. Consumer side: child repo hooks, `session\ncurrent/list`, and `session attach` all resolve session state through the\ncwd's git common dir, so they cannot discover a session registered somewhere\nelse. Strongest evidence: live `entire session list --json` and `entire\nsession current --json` from `devenv/` return no sessions, while the CLI\nsource (`session/state.go:379-386`, `strategy/session_state.go:78-114`,\n`hooks_git_cmd.go:67-75`) shows the reader/hook paths are repo-scoped; a\nskill can attach a known session id into child repos, but the exact\nzero-prerequisite workflow needs a repo-independent current-session-id\nsource before the skill can be reliable.\n\n## Question\n\nContext: I use entire to track all agent sessions but entire is repo based\nProblem: I often run my agents in a higher level folder so it can work across repos. For example /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv then have agents make changes across different folders/repos opening worktrees. But then my agent sessions don't get tracked by entire in the repos\nSolution: is there a skill you can build that fixes this issue? it should use entire commands to do this. if it needs a new entire command let me know and I will consider building it.\n\n## Prior work\n\nSearched Entire for prior discussion of this problem:\n\n- `entire search \"session tracking across repos worktree\" --json` — no\n  direct hit on multi-repo session capture. Closest hit was the\n  `session-handoff` work around checkpoint `78618657a89b`.\n- `entire search \"cross-repo agent session worktree devenv\"` — only the\n  same handoff thread.\n- `entire search \"external agents on PATH\"` and\n  `entire search \"attach session\"` — only the handoff thread; no separate\n  prior skill or command surface for \"attach one parent-launched session to\n  multiple child repos\".\n- Round 1 Codex reran phrase-from-symptom searches:\n  - `entire search \"sessions don't get tracked by entire in the repos\"\n    --json` — session-handoff checkpoints `78618657a89b`,\n    `80109082dc65`, and the version-bump checkpoint `461b2ad0a096`.\n  - `entire search \"agents in a higher level folder across repos\" --json`\n    — session-handoff checkpoint `78618657a89b` plus version bump\n    `461b2ad0a096`.\n  - `entire search \"track all agent sessions repo based cross repo\" --json`\n    — the same session-handoff/version-bump cluster.\n- Round 2 Codex searched the symptom phrase again:\n  - `entire search \"agent sessions don't get tracked by entire in the repos\"\n    --json` — the same three session-handoff/version-bump checkpoints.\n  - `entire search \"higher level folder across repos sessions don't get\n    tracked\" --json` — the same cluster, including a historical snippet\n    claiming `entire session list --json` returned sessions \"across all\n    worktrees.\" That claim is stale or context-limited; current source and\n    command output below show `session list` reads the cwd repo's git common\n    dir store, not a global registry.\n\nThe prior work is useful historical context only. I inspected the associated\ncommit messages for their `Entire-Checkpoint:` trailers and tried the required\nexplain step with both `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --no-pager` and\n`entire checkpoint explain --checkpoint <id> --search-all --no-pager`; every\nattempt for `78618657a89b`, `80109082dc65`, and `461b2ad0a096` failed with\n`checkpoint not found: <id>`. Current CLI/source verification below therefore\ntakes precedence over the search snippets. In particular, the first draft's\n\"global session registry\" inference is not supported by the current code or\ncommands.\n\n## System under investigation\n\n```\nProducer side:\n\n  Agent CLI launched from /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv\n        |\n        v\n  Entire session hooks resolve cwd's git repo/common dir\n        |\n        v\n  /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv is not Entire-enabled\n  (.entire/settings.json missing; .git/entire-sessions absent)\n        |\n        v\n  No parent session state for `entire session current/list` to find\n\nConsumer side:\n\n  Agent edits/commits under child repos:\n      devenv/cli/        devenv/entire.io/        devenv/entiredb/\n      (each has its own .git and .entire/settings.json; all are\n       gitignored by the parent devenv repo)\n        |\n        v\n  Child repo post-commit hook / attach consumer reads only that child's\n  git common dir:\n      <child>/.git/entire-sessions/*.json\n        |\n        v\n  Parent-launched session is absent from the child store, so no\n  Entire-Checkpoint trailer is linked to the child's commits.\n\nManual recovery primitive:\n\n  known session id + target child repo\n        |\n        v\n  (cd target && entire session attach <session-id> --force)\n        |\n        v\n  Reads agent transcript, redacts/writes checkpoint metadata, amends\n  target repo HEAD with Entire-Checkpoint trailer\n        |\n        v\n  Cost amplification on bad discovery/retry:\n      per target attempt = transcript read/redaction + checkpoint write/fetch\n      + possible commit amend of the wrong repo's HEAD. Existing CLI has no\n      --target-repo, --dry-run, or repo-independent \"current agent session\"\n      command to bound that risk.\n```\n\n## Approach\n\nInspected the Entire CLI surface for `session list`, `session current`,\n`session info`, and `session attach`; verified behavior from three cwd\nlocations (`scope-skill`, `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv`, and\n`/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli`); and read the CLI source for session\nstate storage, current-session selection, and attach. Also verified the\nuser's actual directory layout: `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv` is a git\nrepo without `.entire/settings.json`, and `cli/`, `entire.io/`, and\n`entiredb/` are gitignored independent repos with their own `.git` and\n`.entire/settings.json`.\n\nNo destructive commands were run. I did not run `entire session attach`\nbecause it can amend the target repo's HEAD.\n\n## Findings\n\n### 1. The `devenv/` parent is a separate, non-Entire-enabled repo; the child repos are gitignored independent repos\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/.git/` exists, so `devenv` is a real git\n  repo.\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/.gitignore:1-4` lists `cli/`,\n  `entiredb/`, and `entire.io/` under \"Cloned repositories\".\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/.entire/` contains only `logs/`; no\n  `.entire/settings.json` exists.\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/.git/entire-sessions` does not exist.\n- `cd /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv && entire status --json` returned\n  `{\"enabled\":false,\"agents\":null,\"active_sessions\":null,\"error\":\"not set up\"}`.\n- `cd /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv && entire session current --json`\n  returned `No active session found in this worktree.`\n- `find /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv -maxdepth 3` found child repo\n  settings at:\n  - `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.entire/settings.json`\n  - `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/entire.io/.entire/settings.json`\n  - `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/entiredb/.entire/settings.json`\n\nConclusion for this finding: checkpoints need to land in each child repo's\ncommit history. The parent repo's commit history is the wrong target because\nthe actual code commits happen in gitignored child repos.\n\n### 2. The current CLI does not have a global session registry; `session list` is scoped to the current repo's git common dir\n\nThis disputes the first draft's central claim that `entire session list\n--json` is global across unrelated repos.\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `cd /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv && entire session list --json` returned\n  `[]`.\n- `cd /Users/alisha/.marvin/worktrees/skills/scope-skill && entire session\n  list --json` returned only skills-repo sessions, including\n  `ff4ae70d-2f63-4057-a175-1183b6fe1f8e`.\n- `cd /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli && entire session list --json`\n  returned cli-repo sessions, including active/idle sessions rooted at\n  `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli` and\n  `/Users/alisha/.marvin/worktrees/cli/entire-labs-investigate`.\n- Source confirms the behavior: `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/sessions.go:340`\n  calls `strategy.ListSessionStates`, and\n  `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go:377`\n  creates the store from `getGitCommonDir`.\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go:609`\n  runs `git rev-parse --git-common-dir`, then stores sessions under\n  `<common-dir>/entire-sessions` at\n  `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go:384-385`.\n- The apparent cross-worktree visibility inside `devenv/cli` is explained\n  by shared git common dir, not by a global registry:\n  `git -C /Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli rev-parse --git-common-dir`\n  returned `.git`, and\n  `git -C /Users/alisha/.marvin/worktrees/cli/entire-labs-investigate\n  rev-parse --git-common-dir` returned\n  `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.git`.\n\nConclusion for this finding: a skill invoked from `devenv/` cannot recover\nthe current parent-launched session by asking a child repo's `entire session\nlist`. The child repo cannot see the parent's store, and the parent currently\nhas no store entries.\n\n### 3. Producer failure: if the agent starts in the non-enabled parent, there may be no Entire session id to attach\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/.git/entire-sessions` is absent; a direct\n  `find .git/entire-sessions -maxdepth 1 -type f` from the parent failed\n  with `No such file or directory`.\n- `entire session current --json` from the parent returned no active session,\n  and `entire session list --json` from the parent returned `[]`.\n- `FindMostRecentSession` is intentionally current-worktree oriented:\n  `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/session_state.go:91-114`\n  scopes by `paths.WorktreeRoot` when possible.\n- `paths.WorktreeRoot` is based on `git rev-parse --show-toplevel`\n  (`/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/paths/paths.go:87-115`),\n  so a launch from `devenv/` resolves to the parent repo, not to a child\n  repo the agent later edits.\n\nThis is the producer side of the failure. The agent session must be created\nsomewhere before `entire session attach <session-id>` can be used reliably.\nIf `devenv/` is not Entire-enabled and the agent runtime does not expose its\nnative session id through an Entire command, the skill has no trustworthy\nsession id to pass to `attach`.\n\n### 4. Consumer failure: child repo hooks and `attach` read/write only the target repo, so they cannot infer a parent-launched session\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `entire session attach --help` says it \"creates a checkpoint from the\n  session's transcript and links it to the last commit\"; no `--target-repo`,\n  `--commit`, or `--dry-run` flag is exposed.\n- Hook logging is repo-gated and repo-scoped: `hooks_git_cmd.go:67` returns\n  immediately when the cwd repo is not set up/enabled, and\n  `hooks_git_cmd.go:75` asks `strategy.FindMostRecentSession(ctx)` for the\n  session id in that same cwd.\n- `session current` follows the same consumer path:\n  `session_current.go:42-44` calls `strategy.FindMostRecentSession(ctx)` and\n  prints \"No active session found in this worktree\" when it returns empty.\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go:91` exits early\n  only if the target repo is disabled; otherwise all work is for the current\n  cwd.\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go:576-594`\n  validates the session against the current repo and opens the current repo's\n  session store.\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go:606-617`\n  resolves and reads the transcript after a session id is already known.\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go:489-501`\n  reuses a checkpoint trailer already on HEAD or generates a new checkpoint\n  id, and `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go:730-734`\n  amends the current repo's HEAD commit.\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go:581-582`\n  requires at least one commit in the target repo.\n\nConsumer-side cost/risk per bad attempt: once a skill guesses a target repo\nand session id, attach can read/redact the transcript, write checkpoint\nmetadata, fetch checkpoint metadata if HEAD already references a checkpoint,\nand amend the target repo's last commit. That makes \"try a bunch of child\nrepos until one works\" the wrong failure mode; the skill needs strong target\nrepo and session-id evidence before invoking attach.\n\nSymmetric consequence (verified): even if the parent `devenv/` were\nEntire-enabled with a registered session, child repo git hooks would still\nnot pick it up automatically. `strategy.FindMostRecentSession`\n(`devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/session_state.go:95-114`) and\n`strategy.ListSessionStates`\n(`devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/session_state.go:78-89`) both construct\nthe store via `session.NewStateStore`, which resolves the git common dir of\nthe hook's cwd — i.e., the child repo at commit time. Parent-enabled by\nitself solves only the producer half; the consumer (child repo hook /\nattach) needs the parent's session id pushed into the child repo's store\nbefore the child's commit hook fires.\n\n### 5. Existing commands can support a constrained skill, but not the exact zero-prerequisite parent-dir workflow\n\nVerified usable pieces:\n\n- If the skill already has a valid session id, it can run\n  `entire session attach <session-id> --force` inside each affected child repo.\n- If the launch cwd is Entire-enabled, `entire session current --json` can\n  expose the current session id and `worktree_path`.\n- `entire session info <id> --json` can expose `files_touched` for sessions\n  that are in the current repo's session store; confirmed from\n  `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/entire.io`, where `session current --json`\n  included `files_touched` entries such as\n  `api/src/lib/transcript-parsers/amp-parser.ts`.\n\nVerified gaps:\n\n- From the user's concrete parent cwd (`/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv`), the\n  existing `session current/list` commands return no session data.\n- From a child repo, `session current/list` sees only that repo clone's git\n  common-dir states, not the parent repo.\n- `~/.entire/registered-repos.json` is not a complete discovery source on\n  this machine: it contains `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli`, but not\n  `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/entire.io` or\n  `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/entiredb`, even though both child repos have\n  `.entire/settings.json` and `entire status --json` reports enabled in\n  `entiredb` and `entire.io`.\n\nConclusion for this finding: a skill can ship only with a clear prerequisite\nor explicit input: either the parent launch repo must be Entire-enabled before\nthe agent run starts, or the user/agent must provide the native session id.\nFor the exact \"I launched from a higher-level folder and now the child repos\ndid not track it\" symptom, existing commands are missing a repo-independent\nway to ask \"what is the current agent session id?\" A `--target-repo` flag\nwould reduce attach orchestration risk, but it does not solve the missing\nsession-id producer gap by itself.\n\n### 6. One local CLI/settings mismatch can cause false negatives during repo detection\n\nThis is not the root cause of the parent-dir problem, but it matters for a\nskill that audits child repos before attaching.\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.entire/settings.local.json:1-10`\n  sets `\"enabled\": false` and includes an `\"investigate\"` object.\n- The installed CLI (`Entire CLI 0.6.2`) reports from `devenv/cli`:\n  `{\"enabled\":false,\"agents\":null,\"active_sessions\":null,\"error\":\"failed to load settings: loading settings: merging local settings: parsing JSON: json: unknown field \\\"investigate\\\"\"}`.\n- The current source explains why: settings use strict JSON decoding with\n  `DisallowUnknownFields` in\n  `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/settings/settings.go:469-472`\n  and again for local overrides at\n  `/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/settings/settings.go:551-557`.\n- `checkDisabledGuard` defaults to enabled on settings-load errors\n  (`/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/setup.go:1199-1204`),\n  so `attach` may still run, while `status` reports an error.\n\nConclusion for this finding: a skill should not use `entire status --json`\nalone as the authoritative \"can I attach here?\" signal. Presence of a git repo\nplus `.entire/settings.json`, the actual `attach` preflight result, and a\nclear skip/error reason are more reliable than assuming `status` failures mean\n\"not an Entire repo.\"\n\n## Unknowns / Assumptions\n\n- **Not reproduced by spawning a fresh agent from `devenv/`**: current\n  evidence shows no existing parent session states and source says the\n  state store is repo/common-dir scoped. I did not start a new Claude/Codex\n  run from `devenv/` to watch the hook lifecycle live.\n- **Attach idempotency not exercised**: source shows `promptAmendCommit`\n  skips appending an identical checkpoint trailer already on HEAD, and\n  attach reuses an existing session state's checkpoint when present. I did\n  not run attach twice because it can amend commits.\n- **Affected-repo detection remains partly design work**: for a parent-enabled\n  future run, `files_touched` may be enough for apply-patch paths under the\n  parent, but worktrees opened outside the parent (`~/.marvin/worktrees/...`)\n  and shell-created files need separate handling or explicit repo input.\n- **CLI command shape is not settled**: the evidence supports a missing\n  repo-independent \"current agent session id\" command as the main gap, plus\n  `attach --target-repo` / `--commit` / `--dry-run` as consumer-side\n  risk reducers. The exact command names are still a design decision.\n\n## Conclusion\n\nConsensus: the investigation is complete. Existing Entire commands can support\na constrained scope skill only when it already has a trustworthy session id, or\nwhen the parent launch repo is Entire-enabled before the agent run starts and\nthe skill can explicitly attach that session into the affected child repos. The\ncommands do not support the exact zero-prerequisite parent-directory workflow\nafter the fact: the parent has no session state, the child repos cannot see\noutside their own git-common-dir stores, and `attach` has no target/dry-run\nsurface to make blind multi-repo attempts cheap or safe."},"uuid":"69a60e9d-1d51-4d38-8dbd-287dd1fcb607","timestamp":"2026-05-19T18:21:30.344Z","permissionMode":"default","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/.marvin/worktrees/skills/scope-skill","sessionId":"f3d53121-fdf7-40bf-a4df-e3b17ddbbbd1","version":"2.1.144","gitBranch":"scope-skill","sessionKind":"bg"}
