{"parentUuid":"1f64b91b-8c91-43a4-845a-f3cbdb51b10a","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01HGSoEeRUkmeBhEStD12Xqw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the concrete sketch.\n\n## Skill: `entire-scope` (proposed name)\n\n**Trigger:** User says something like \"attach my session to the child repos\", or runs `/entire-scope` at end of an agent run that touched files across multiple repos under a non-Entire-enabled parent.\n\n**Precondition:** Parent launch dir must be Entire-enabled. If not, the skill prints the one-line setup command and stops. (No retrofit attempt — without a parent session store there's nothing to attach.)\n\n**Flow:**\n\n1. **Resolve session.** `entire session current --json` from parent → `session_id`, `worktree_path`, `files_touched`. If no current session, fall back to most-recent from `entire session list --json` in parent, filtered by time window. Bail if zero.\n\n2. **Discover affected child repos.** Build the candidate set from three sources, union them:\n   - For each path in `files_touched`: walk up to nearest `.git` dir, record toplevel.\n   - `git -C <parent> status --porcelain` of any submodule-like child dirs that have their own `.git`.\n   - Optional explicit input: `--repos /path/a,/path/b` for shell-created files or out-of-tree worktrees the skill can't infer.\n\n   Filter to repos that have `.entire/settings.json` AND `entire status --json` reports enabled (with finding-6's caveat: also accept the case where `status` fails on `unknown field` but attach preflight succeeds).\n\n3. **Preview plan.** For each candidate repo, call the new `entire session attach <id> --target-repo <path> --dry-run --json`. Skill renders a table:\n\n   ```\n   repo                              HEAD commit   trailer action   transcript bytes\n   devenv/cli                        a1b2c3d       ADD              42KB\n   devenv/entire.io                  e4f5g6h       SKIP (existing)  —\n   devenv/entiredb                   (no commits)  ERROR            —\n   ```\n\n4. **Confirm + execute.** User confirms; skill runs `entire session attach <id> --target-repo <path> --force` per repo. Reports success/failure per row. Idempotent — re-running is safe (existing-trailer rows stay SKIP).\n\n5. **Persist scope record.** Write a small artifact to the parent's `.entire/logs/` so a later `/what-happened` or `entire session info` can tell which child repos got linked.\n\n---\n\n## New Entire CLI surface needed\n\n### 1. `entire session attach --target-repo <path>` (required)\n\nCurrently attach implicitly uses cwd's git common dir. Add an explicit flag so the skill never has to `cd`. Resolves the repo's git common dir from `<path>` rather than `os.Getwd()`.\n\n- Validates `<path>` is a git repo with `.entire/settings.json`.\n- All HEAD lookups, transcript writes, and amend operations happen against `<path>`.\n- Errors clearly when `<path>` has no commits, isn't Entire-enabled, or session id isn't in that repo's store yet (in which case attach copies session state from the source repo's store — see #3).\n\n### 2. `entire session attach --dry-run --json` (required)\n\nPrint what would happen without amending. Output JSON:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"session_id\": \"ff4ae70d-...\",\n  \"target_repo\": \"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\n  \"head_commit\": \"a1b2c3d\",\n  \"existing_trailer\": null,\n  \"action\": \"would_add_trailer\" | \"would_skip_existing\" | \"would_error\",\n  \"error\": null,\n  \"checkpoint_id_planned\": \"ckpt_...\",\n  \"transcript_bytes\": 42000\n}\n```\n\nSkill aggregates these into the preview table in step 3.\n\n### 3. Cross-repo session-state visibility (required, biggest change)\n\nAttach needs to read session state for `<session-id>` even when the target repo's git-common-dir store doesn't have it yet. Two implementation options:\n\n- **(a) `--source-repo <path>` flag** — explicit \"look in this repo's store for the session, write checkpoint into target's store.\" Smallest CLI change; skill always passes `--source-repo <parent>`.\n- **(b) Implicit lookup via `~/.entire/registered-repos.json`** — attach scans known registered repos for the session id. Cleaner UX but requires the registry to be complete (finding 5 noted it currently isn't).\n\nRecommend (a) — explicit, no registry dependency, matches how the skill already knows the parent path.\n\n### 4. `entire session attach --commit <sha>` (nice-to-have)\n\nIf the agent made multiple commits in a child repo, the skill can attach the trailer to a specific one instead of just HEAD. Without this, the skill can only link the most recent commit per repo.\n\n---\n\n## What stays out of scope\n\n- **Zero-prereq retrofit** (parent never had Entire enabled). Skipped — no producer-side session state to recover.\n- **Auto-detection of worktrees outside the parent tree.** Handled via the `--repos` opt-in flag instead of magic discovery.\n- **Linking *all* commits in a child repo to the same session.** Skill links one commit per repo (HEAD, or `--commit`). Multi-commit linking is a separate feature.\n\n---\n\n**Minimum to ship:** flags #1, #2, #3a on the Entire side; skill calls them in the flow above. That's ~3 small flags + one new code path for cross-store reads. Flag #4 can be a fast-follow if the one-commit-per-repo limit bites in practice.\n\nWant me to drop this into a design doc in the repo, or start drafting the SKILL.md against the assumption these flags will exist?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":212,"cache_read_input_tokens":43248,"output_tokens":3099,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":212,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":3099,"cache_read_input_tokens":43248,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2