ailable) + git status walks + optional `--repos` flag for out-of-tree paths.\n\n**Updated flow:**\n\n1. Skill resolves its own native session id from the runtime it's in.\n2. Skill discovers affected Entire-enabled repos (any combination — current repo, sibling repos, child repos under a non-Entire parent, worktrees elsewhere).\n3. For each: `entire session attach <session-id> --target-repo <path> --dry-run --json` → render preview.\n4. On confirmation: same call without `--dry-run`.\n\nOne thing to confirm: does Entire have any way to expose \"what's the session id of the agent currently running this skill\" without runtime-specific knowledge baked into the skill? If not, the skill needs a tiny per-runtime adapter (Claude Code / Codex / etc.). That's the only remaining open question.\n\nWant me to write this up as a design doc, or start on the SKILL.md?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1448,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3080,"cache_read_input_tokens":49557,"output_tokens":2219,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3080,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1448,"output_tokens":2219,"cache_read_input_tokens":49557,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3080,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3080},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CbCREVcddb8uzMc3NckZo","type":"assistant","uuid":"13045db5-3c70-47b0-8726-57b59ebb0a67","timestamp":"2026-05-19T18:42:27.957Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/.marvin/worktrees/skills/scope-skill","sessionId":"f3d53121-fdf7-40bf-a4df-e3b17ddbbbd1","version":"2.1.144","gitBranch":"scope-skill","sessionKind":"bg"}
