{"parentUuid":"603234bf-d7bc-4bf4-90ea-000e70554462","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01HqDfhbc8cLx64MiFqnZJA6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01D9z2kU7Um96gDMVZKLR6M4","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"gh pr edit 26 --title \"feat(session-crosslink): add skill for cross-repo session attach\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\n\nAdds the `session-crosslink` skill — an agent-invokable workflow that attaches an agent session to one or more Entire-enabled repos whose commits should record it, even when the agent ran from somewhere else (a higher-level folder, a non-Entire repo, or one repo while editing another).\n\n## What this solves\n\nEntire tracks agent sessions per repo via state stored under each repo's git common dir. When an agent runs from `~/Projects/devenv` (a non-Entire-enabled parent), and edits multiple child repos (`devenv/cli`, `devenv/entire.io`, etc.), none of the child repos see the session — their commits don't get `Entire-Checkpoint:` trailers. The same problem happens when an agent in repo X needs to update repo Y.\n\nThis skill resolves the agent session id from whichever source has it (Entire's per-repo state, a sibling repo's state, or the agent runtime's transcript directory), discovers which Entire-enabled repos were affected, runs `entire session attach --target-repo <path> --dry-run --json` per repo to render a preview, and on user confirmation re-runs without `--dry-run` to amend each repo's HEAD.\n\n## Depends on\n\nThis skill calls `entire session attach` with flags introduced in entireio/cli#1229:\n- `--target-repo <path>` — operate on a specific repo without `cd`.\n- `--dry-run [--json]` — preview the plan (action, checkpoint id, transcript size) without amending.\n\nMerge the CLI PR first; this skill will fail with \"flag rejected\" until that ships.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] Install the skill locally (`npx skills add file:// ... --skill session-crosslink`) and invoke it from this repo (Entire-enabled) — verify it resolves session via `entire session current --json`.\n- [ ] Invoke from a non-Entire-enabled parent (`~/Projects/devenv`) with a Claude Code session — verify the Strategy C transcript-directory fallback finds the session id.\n- [ ] Invoke with a session that has files touched across two Entire-enabled repos — verify the preview table shows both, with correct actions and checkpoint ids.\n- [ ] Confirm + execute — verify each repo's HEAD gets an \\`Entire-Checkpoint:\\` trailer.\n- [ ] Re-invoke immediately — verify idempotency (all rows report \\`would_skip_existing_in_state\\`).\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1 | tail -3","description":"Update skill PR title and body","timeout":30000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":391,"cache_read_input_tokens":244143,"output_tokens":2590,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":391,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":2590,"cache_read_input_tokens":244143,"cache_creation_input_tokens":391,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":391},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CbCZKRdLx71XardhFNey3","type":"assistant","uuid":"96dbaa81-7e46-421a-97d4-e7bfc1972e9a","timestamp":"2026-05-19T20:28:09.325Z","sessionKind":"bg","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/alisha/.marvin/worktrees/skills/scope-skill","sessionId":"f3d53121-fdf7-40bf-a4df-e3b17ddbbbd1","version":"2.1.144","gitBranch":"scope-skill","slug":"virtual-wibbling-popcorn"}
